ul.li:
                        ToolWindowType.SLIDING
                        - When SLIDING type is used, the tool window overlaps the main frame and/or other tool windows.
                        When it loses focus, the tool window hides itself.


To set ToolWindowType.SLIDING type use the following:
                        ToolWindow toolWindow = toolWindowManager.getToolWindow("Debug Tool");
toolWindow.setType(ToolWindowType.SLIDING);

                        ToolWindowType.FLOATING_WINDOW
                        This type differs from FLOATING type for the absence of the representative button
                        on the tool window bar.


To set ToolWindowType.FLOATING_WINDOW type use the following:
                        ToolWindow toolWindow = toolWindowManager.getToolWindow("Debug Tool");
toolWindow.setType(ToolWindowType.FLOATING_WINDOW);

                        DockedTypeDescriptor
                        This interface is used to modify the behaviours of DOCKED type.


To get a DockedTypeDescriptor instance use the following:
                        ToolWindow toolWindow = toolWindowManager.getToolWindow("Debug Tool");
DockedTypeDescriptor dockedTypeDescriptor = (DockedTypeDescriptor) toolWindow.getTypeDescriptor(ToolWindowType.DOCKED);

                        FloatingTypeDescriptor
                        This interface is used to modify the behaviours of FLOATING and FLOATING_WINDOW type.


To get a DockedTypeDescriptor instance use the following:
                        ToolWindow toolWindow = toolWindowManager.getToolWindow("Debug Tool");
FloatingTypeDescriptor typeDescriptor = (FloatingTypeDescriptor) toolWindowManager.getTypeDescriptorTemplate(ToolWindowType.FLOATING);
